#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"\n"
"Master Production Schedule\n"
"==========================\n"
"\n"
"Sometimes you need to create the purchase orders for the components of\n"
"manufacturing orders that will only be created later.  Or for production "
"orders\n"
"where you will only have the sales orders later.  The solution is to "
"predict\n"
"your sale forecasts and based on that you will already create some "
"production\n"
"orders or purchase orders.\n"
"\n"
"You need to choose the products you want to add to the report.  You can "
"choose\n"
"the period for the report: day, week, month, ...  It is also possible to "
"define\n"
"safety stock, minimum to supply and to manually override the amount you "
"will\n"
"procure.\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Hovedproduktionsplan\n"
"==========================\n"
"\n"
"I nogle situationer er det nødvendigt at oprette indkøbsordrer til "
"komponenter for\n"
"produktionsordrer, der først oprettes senere, eller for produktionsordrer,\n"
"hvor salgsordrerne endnu ikke er oprettet. Løsningen er at bruge "
"salgsprognoser\n"
"til at planlægge og oprette produktions-\n"
"eller indkøbsordrer på forhånd.\n"
"\n"
"Du kan vælge, hvilke produkter der skal med i rapporten, og angive\n"
"perioden for rapporten – dag, uge, måned osv. Det er også muligt at "
"definere\n"
"sikkerhedslager, minimumsbeholdning og manuelt justere de mængder, der skal\n"
"indkøbes.\n"

